President Trump delivered remarks at the State Department, thanking the Global Coalition to Defeat ISIS for their commitment to fighting against the terrorist organization. He highlighted the progress made in liberating territory previously held by ISIS in Syria and Iraq, and the elimination of top ISIS leaders. The President commended the United States military and coalition partners for their efforts in decimating the ISIS caliphate. He also emphasized the importance of continuing to search out and eliminate remaining ISIS remnants and preventing the spread of radical Islamic terrorism. The President expressed gratitude to the coalition members and pledged to continue working together to address the ongoing threat of terrorism.